result.execSummary:
The defendant Aissa Oumarou was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Aissa  Oumarou in court, in custody, with attorney Maura Ann Mcmahon.   Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Interpreter, Paula Loubier, appeared in court.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Defense makes sentencing recommendations.  The defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count 1:

JAIL:  105 days,  (Credit - 103 days). 
Court takes good time credit when making this sentence and orders that the defendant is to serve 2 days in the jail commencing forthwith.
Defendant is remanded back to the Waukesha County Jail.

COSTS: $243.00 
DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Court orders that the costs and DNA surcharge are to be converted to a civil judgment.

Count 2:

JAIL:  90 days,  (Credit - 90 days).   Court considers time served.
Sentence is to run concurrent with Count 1.

COSTS: $243.00 
DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Court applies 10-days jail credit to the costs and DNA surcharge.  Court considers costs and DNA surcharge paid in full.
